{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f9775221-d6b8-459f-90c9-b135658819e5","content":"In .NET MAUI, `OnStart`/`OnSleep`/`OnResume` no longer exist on `Application`. Instead, use **window lifecycle events** via `CreateWindow`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = new Window(new MainPage());\n\n    window.Created += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnStart */ };\n    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnSleep */ };\n    window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnResume */ };\n    window.Destroying += (s, e) => { /* cleanup on close */ };\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Lifecycle is now **per-window**, not per-app (MAUI supports multi-window).\n- Additional events available: `Activated`, `Deactivated`, `Backgrounding`.\n- For **platform-specific** lifecycle hooks, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android.OnStop(activity => { /* ... */ }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios.DidEnterBackground(app => { /* ... */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe7e3998-45b8-425a-80d7-0c066a5822a0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` in your `Application` subclass. In .NET MAUI, these still exist on `Application`, but the recommended approach is to use the **lifecycle events** via the `Window` class or configure them through `CreateWindow`.\n\nLet me give a concise answer.","outputTokens":469},"id":"c4dc02ac-283b-4e8d-9ccc-6dad3fa28643","timestamp":"2026-04-09T15:19:37.408Z","parentId":"b83587c6-5daf-4344-96f2-65e11c0c7dc1"}
